<div class="faq_card">
    <h2>FAQ - CoinTribe</h2>

    <h3>1. Account Registration and Management</h3>
    <h4>1.1 How can I register on the platform?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        To register, click the "Sign Up" button on the homepage. You must provide a valid email address and accept the Terms of Use (CGU) and Privacy Policy.
    </p>
    <h4>1.2 Is registration mandatory to use the services?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        No, you can browse and search cryptocurrencies without creating an account. However, features like voting or commenting require registration.
    </p>
    <h4>1.3 How do I change my pseudonym?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        You can change your pseudonym anytime from your personal space by clicking on your profile.
    </p>
    <h4>1.4 How do I delete my account?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        To delete your account, go to the settings in your personal space and select the "Delete My Account" option. This action is irreversible and will permanently delete all your data (votes, posts, comments, pseudonym).
    </p>
    <h4>1.5 What happens when I delete my account?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        All personal data associated with your account, including votes, posts and comments, will be permanently deleted. These details cannot be recovered.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="faq_card">
    <h3>2. Features and Services</h3>
    <h4>2.1 What features are accessible without registration?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        Without registration, you can:
    </p>
    <ul class="faq_text">
        <li>Explore the list of available cryptocurrencies.</li>
        <li>Search for specific cryptocurrencies by name or symbol.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>2.2 How does the Bullish and Bearish voting system work?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        As a registered user, you can express your opinion on a cryptocurrency by voting "Bullish" (optimistic) or "Bearish" (pessimistic). Each user can vote once every 24 hours per cryptocurrency.
    </p>
    <h4>2.3 Can I modify my vote once it is submitted?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        No, once your vote is submitted, it cannot be modified. You will be able to vote again after 24 hours.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="faq_card">
    <h3>3. Privacy and Security</h3>
    <h4>3.1 What personal data do you collect?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">We collect:</p>
    <ul class="faq_text">
        <li>Your email address for account management.</li>
        <li>Your pseudonym to identify your contributions.</li>
        <li>Your votes, comments, and publications.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>3.2 Why do you collect my personal data?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">Your data is collected to:</p>
    <ul class="faq_text">
        <li>Manage your user account.</li>
        <li>Enable voting, commenting, and interactions on the platform.</li>
        <li>Improve the user experience.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>3.3 How is my data protected?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">We use:</p>
    <ul class="faq_text">
        <li>Password encryption.</li>
        <li>Secure protocols like HTTPS/SSL.</li>
        <li>Regular backups to prevent data loss.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>3.4 Do you share my data with third parties?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        No, your personal data is not sold to third parties. It may only be shared with technical service providers for the proper functioning of the site (e.g., hosting).
    </p>
    <h4>3.5 How can I request a copy of my personal data?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        You can contact us at 'CoinTribe@yopmail.com' to request a copy of your data. Proof of identity may be required.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="faq_card">
    <h3>4. Cookies and Tracking</h3>
    <h4>4.1 What types of cookies do you use?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">We use only functional cookies necessary for the proper functioning of the site (e.g., login, navigation).</p>
    <h4>4.2 Can I disable cookies?</h4>
    
    <p class="faq_text">You can configure your browser to block cookies, but this may limit some essential site functionalities.</p>
    <h4>4.3 Do you use advertising or analytics cookies?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">No, we do not currently use advertising or analytics cookies. If this changes, a GDPR-compliant consent banner will be implemented.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq_card">
    <h3>5. Moderation and Community</h3>
    <h4>5.1 Who can comment on cryptocurrencies?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">Only registered users can post comments or respond to existing posts.</p>
    <h4>5.2 How is content moderated on the platform?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        All user-generated content is regularly moderated to ensure compliance with our community rules.
    </p>
    <h4>5.3 Can I report a comment or post?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        Yes, a reporting system is available. Our moderation team will review reports promptly.
    </p>
    <h4>5.4 What community rules must I follow?</h4>
    <ul class="faq_text">
        <li>No hate speech or discriminatory content.</li>
        <li>No spam or fraudulent content.</li>
        <li>Respect the opinions of other users.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>5.5 What happens if a user posts inappropriate content?</h4>
    <p class="faq_text">
        Reported content is reviewed by our team. Users posting non-compliant content may receive a warning or have their account suspended.
    </p>
</div>

